args: Oh, apologies! I don't mean to sound\nunappreciative after you brought me\nall the way out here.

But when you said their harvest festival
was supposed to be extraordinarily
exciting, I was expecting something a
little...larger.
That's natural. To be honest, I don't know\nmany specifics of the festival myself.
I'm guessing it involves that log they're\nsetting up in the middle of the street?
Just a biiiit higher... Perfect!\nFix it in place there!
I can't think of many uses for a log hanging\nhorizontally just above everyone's heads.
I thought it might be to hold up the roof of\na temporary building, but it's too low.
Either way, we should go speak with the\nvillage chief. We'll need his permission\nto set off those pyroblossoms.
I suppose we can ask him about the\nfestival while we're there.
I understand that pyroblossoms can be\nrather loud and startling—and perhaps\neven dangerous in untrained hands.

But that's why I will take every precaution
to ensure the people's safety. I will also
let every villager know what's going on
in advance so they aren't scared.
Oh, well that makes me feel ALL better!
＂Hey there, Chief! I know you've never\nmet us before, but do you mind if we\nfire off a bunch of EXPLOSIVES?!＂
W-well, when you put it that way...
I'm with the chief. This is a terrible idea.
This is OUR festival, outsiders.\nNow make like an egg and beat it!
Now hold on! If you just knew what he\nwas trying to do here, I'm sure—
No, it's all right. What they're saying\nis perfectly reasonable.
Well, at least one of you has sense.\nNow make like a bakery wagon\nand haul some buns outta here!
I'm not going anywhere; I will find some\nother way to take part in your festival.
I might not be from this village, but I still\nwant this festival to be a success.
If you then find me to be worthy of\nyour trust, perhaps we can revisit\nthe matter of my request.
I dunno about this guy, Chief.\nHe's making like a tree—shady!
Tell me something, Su Fang. Why are you\nso obsessed with these pyroblossoms of\nyours?
Because I want to make people happy!
Very well. I'll permit your participation—\nand for you to set off your pyroblossoms.
You must win one of our festival's\ntraditional contests!
So the competitors race to the dangling\nbread, and then try to grab a piece using\nonly their mouths?
So THAT'S what the log is for!
Yep! It's the best part of the festival.\nIt ALSO happens to be my best event,\nwhich is sad luck for you! Bwa ha ha!
Now make like a loser and lose!
Uh oh. It sounds like he's really\ngood at...er, whatever this is.\nAND I think he's in your group!
He will be a formidable opponent,\nbut I will not lose.
Looks like Su Fang's group goes next.
They're neck-and-neck on the race part,\nbut here comes the bread!
This guy ain't bad... I better make\nlike a ladder and step it up!
Uh oh. He's really good at jumping.\nBuuut...
I'm going to jump further! Haaaaaah!
Su Fang got the bread first!\nNow he just needs to make it to the end!
But his opponent's right on his tail...\nAugh! I almost can't look!
So this is what pyroblossoms look like.\nGotta say, they're pretty great.
I was motived by your dedication, Su Fang.\nI could tell how badly you wanted this.
I apologize for saying you weren't worthy\nof trust—and I thank you for what you did.
In fact, I'm wondering if you might be\nwilling to come back next year?
(Pyroblossoms can never bloom where\nthere is no trust. I see that now.)
(So I won't rush things—I'll spread\nthem patiently, little by little.)
Er, hello. I'm sorry for stopping your\nannual winning streak.
You DID do that, didn't you?\nWhich means...
You gotta come back next year\nso I can BEAT you!
I'll be waiting for you, Su Fang.\nNow make like a boot and...um...\nhave a real safe trip home.
Oh, you will see me again for certain.
I wouldn't miss this for the world!
